Name: Christopher Dubeau

The program dirsweeper is a directory cleaner that eather removes files that are older than a
given time or remove files till a directory is under a given size. The program uses fork to
call multiple children processes to watch multiple directories at a single time.

Commands:
	make: will create the dirsweeper executable
	
	make clean: removes all non essential files(.o files and dirsweeper after execution)

Command line:

	To begin the dirsweeper the structure of "dirsweeper [FileName]" where the lone
command line argument is the pathname to a configuration file.

